{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f24e928e-c338-4a75-be30-36f50dfdc196","content":"No files found in the working directory. Since there's no existing file, here's how to convert your page to compiled bindings:\n\n## Compiled Bindings with `x:DataType`\n\nAdd the `x:DataType` attribute to your `ContentPage`, pointing to your ViewModel type:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\" ?>\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" FontSize=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Slider Minimum=\"10\" Maximum=\"36\"\n                Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is:\n1. Add `xmlns:vm` to import the ViewModel namespace.\n2. Add `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the root element.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\nWith `x:DataType` set, the XAML compiler validates bindings against the declared type. A typo like `{Binding Themee}` becomes a **build error**, not a silent runtime failure.\n\nTo ensure this is active, confirm your `.csproj` does **not** disable XAML compilation:\n\n```xml\n<!-- This should NOT be in your .csproj (it disables compiled bindings): -->\n<!-- <MauiXamlCOptOut>true</MauiXamlCOptOut> -->\n```\n\nThat's it — XAML compilation is enabled by default in .NET MAUI. Any binding path that doesn't match a property on `SettingsViewModel` will now produce a compiler error like:\n\n```\nXC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"YourApp.ViewModels.SettingsViewModel\"\n```\n\n**Tip:** If you need to opt out for a specific element (e.g., binding to `BindingContext` set at runtime), use `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` on that element to revert to classic bindings locally.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"97a64c00-ed2d-4b77-9588-3f2ce88883cc","outputTokens":597,"requestId":"503E:1CB4B6:1B3B7A7:1E399C7:69FA8F78"},"id":"8f846080-6d94-434e-87a1-7216e6dee998","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:47:00.311Z","parentId":"f9cb369c-78ed-47e3-b182-d87498463b6c"}
